getElementContents

public static java.lang.String getElementContents(java.lang.String xml,
                                                  java.lang.String name,
                                                  java.lang.String attribute)
Convenience method that just gets the contents of the first element in xml with the given name. If attribute is non-null then that attribute is returned. Note: if attribute is null, the element must be a leaf, i.e. contain only text and have no other children.
